{
  "stem": "19895.8",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, when I came back, survived, I went back to schools to continue education.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Out of the eight years of gymnasium, I still had to finish the seventh and eighth grade.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] well, in September of 1944, the school year didn't start.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] By the way, our school building which I was so proud of, was expropriated by the Hungarian government during the war years, and actual education was in different buildings.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the building itself has a very important spot my memory and my heart.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And years later, we had some reunion when had to school given back to us for one days after I was already an American citizen and we had a Budapest reunion.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When I went back to school from that 56 or so students, about 22 of us was only survived.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "More than half of the students of my class were no longer alive.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And out of that 22, about four of them who were alive, didn't return to school, and didn't want to continue education at that level.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And if we have time, I might mention the story of one of these classmates who didn't return to school, who was a close friend of mine.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we sat in the same bench.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Whom I eventually, many years later, I recovered in the United States, where finally he finished education.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But by then, we could not speak much Hungarian to each other.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He married an American woman and he became an English teacher.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And his Hungarian was very rusty.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That was Thomas Weishaus.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Both of his mother and father died in concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
